  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The CFD solver exposes three tunable configuration parameters — base mesh element size, turbulence-model wall-distance threshold, and hemolysis power-law exponent — that materially affect the predicted relative hemolysis index. Validation results were obtained at the chosen settings for each parameter; however, the package does not pin those settings for deployment and the Context of Use places no constraint on which parameter values must be used in production runs. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-worst-case-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-gcbp-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-cou1-cfd-results-5-operating-points"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou1-cpb",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to identify worst-case operating conditions for hemolysis across 5 flow-speed combinations for a Class II CPB device. Results compared against predicate device hemolysis using relative hemolysis index (RH < 1 acceptance criterion).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Cardiopulmonary bypass use (Class II)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou1-bench-hemolysis-rh",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench hemolysis validation — relative hemolysis index at chosen solver settings",
      "description": "In-vitro hemolysis measurements for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump at five flow-speed operating points were compared against CFD predictions. The model was run at the chosen settings (mesh element size, wall-distance threshold, and power-law exponent) and produced RH values within ±12% of measured values across all operating points, satisfying RH < 1 for the worst-case condition. No record of which specific parameter values were used is included in this package, and no requirement is stated that deployment runs must reproduce these settings."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou1-mesh-convergence-study",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study at the chosen base element size",
      "description": "A three-level mesh refinement study was performed at the chosen base mesh element size (coarse, medium, fine). The medium mesh was selected as the production mesh on the basis of the Grid Convergence Index falling below 2%. The study confirms numerical adequacy at the chosen settings; however, the base element size used to define coarse, medium, and fine levels is not recorded as a pinned deployment parameter."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou1-sensitivity-power-law",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis power-law exponent sensitivity at the chosen threshold",
      "description": "Sensitivity of RH to the hemolysis power-law exponent was evaluated across a ±10% range centred on the chosen value. Results indicate that RH varies by up to 18% across the range, confirming that the exponent is a material configuration parameter. Validation was conducted at the chosen exponent value; the package does not specify this value as a deployment constraint."
    }
  ],
